      <hedline>
        <hl1>Like-Minded Retirees</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Ruth Yanoff letter on April 6 article on retirement communities for people with shared interests</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor: Re ''Birds of a Feather'' (April 6): So let me get this straight. My generation spent much of its collective lifetime rallying against all forms of discrimination and embracing diversity. And now we want these distinct separations in our ''golden'' years so we can be with people just like us. Sounds like we're turning into the ''not in my retirement'' generation. What am I missing here?</p>
        <p>Ruth Yanoff  Springfield, N.J.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
